@@TJvCustomImageButton.AnimateInterval
Summary
  Specifies the interval between the animations.
Description
  Use AnimateInterval to set the number of milliseconds that should pass before a new image is
  displayed on the button when animation is active.
See Also
  TJvCustomImageButton.Animate, TJvCustomImageButton.AnimateFrames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomImageButton.AnimateFrames
Summary
  Specifies how many images are animated when Animate is True.
Description
  Use AnimateFrames to specify how many images in the imagelist are displayed before restarting the
  animation. The animation always starts at the image indicated by the ImageIndex property.
  
  For example, if ImageIndex is set to 0 and AnimateFrames is set to 3, the images with index 0, 1
  and 3 are animated.
See Also
  TJvCustomImageButton.Animate, TJvCustomImageButton.AnimateInterval, TJvCustomImageButton.ImageIndex,
  TJvCustomImageButton.Images

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomImageButton.Alignment
Summary
  Controls the horizontal placement of the text within the control.
Description
  Set Alignment to specify how the text of the control is justified within the ClientRect.
  
  The effect of the Alignment property is more obvious if the WordWrap property is True and the
  control includes more than one line of text.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomImageButton.Animate
Summary
  Specifies if the image on the button is animated
Description
  Set Animate to true to start an animation of the image on the button. To set up the animation, use
  the properties AnimateFrames and AnimateInterval.
See Also
  TJvCustomImageButton.AnimateFrames, TJvCustomImageButton.AnimateInterval,
  TJvCustomImageButton.CurrentAnimateFrame

